courses.learning_outcomes:
Students are expected to
1) Become familiar with current methods used in infectious disease prevention & control;
2) Gain hands-on experience with laboratory-based studies in infectious diseases;
3) Develop skills in epidemiological investigations of infectious disease in the population;
4) Become familiarized with an integrative approach to infectious disease epidemiology.

Through this course students are able to:
1. understand the principle and importance of GIS in public health research;
2. develop a concept understanding of basic GIS in geocoding;
3. conduct basic geostatistical analyses of geo-referenced data of public health and disease mapping in practice;

Student should be able to:
• understand the epidemiology of the major and neglected tropical infectious diseases;
• ability to design, implement and evaluate the control strategy.

Student should be able to:
1. possess the knowledge on surveillance of infectious diseases and infection control in Hong Kong;
2. apply to their future workplace on how to respond to the outbreak of infectious diseases.
